Samson Folarin Suspected hoodlums have set fire to Television Continental, aka TVC, at Ketu, Lagos. A popular talkshow programme, YourView, was on when the hoodlums besieged the station. The programme host, Morayo Afolabi-Brown, who said the hoodlums entered in a van, asked to go on a commercial break. The station had since then been stuck. Videos online confirmed by workers at the station said the assailants set fire to the station over its connection to a former Governor of Lagos State, Bola Tinubu. Temper rose when soldiers besieged the Lekki toll gate on Tuesday night and opened fire on protesters. Eyewitnesses claimed that seven people were confirmed dead and many injured. The incident has been greeted with outrage all over the world.